## Data Access Patterns

### Tours
```typescript
import { tours, getTourBySlug, destinations } from '@/lib/data/tours';

// Get a specific tour
const tour = getTourBySlug('beijing', 'stopover', 'beijing');

// All China tours
const chinaTours = tours.filter(t => t.destination === 'china');
```

### Guides
```typescript
import { getGuideBySlug, getGuidesByParent } from '@/lib/data/guides';

const guide = getGuideBySlug('beijing-travel-guide');
const yunnanSubGuides = getGuidesByParent('yunnan');
```

---

## SEO Requirements — CRITICAL

Every page MUST have:

### 1. Metadata — Use `buildCtsPageMetadata()` helper (REQUIRED)

**Never** hardcode the domain. Always use `buildCtsPageMetadata` from `@/lib/seo-metadata`:

```typescript
import { buildCtsPageMetadata } from '@/lib/seo-metadata';

export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return buildCtsPageMetadata({
    title: 'Specific Page Title | CTS Tours',  // 50-60 chars; " | CTS Tours" auto-appended if missing
    description: 'Unique description per page...',  // 140-160 chars
    path: '/page-slug',                             // site-relative path, starts with /
    ogImagePath: '/images/tours/hero.jpg',          // local path OR absolute https URL
    ogImageAlt: 'Descriptive alt text',
    keywords: ['keyword1', 'keyword2'],
    ogType: 'article',                              // 'article' (default) or 'website'
  });
}
```

`buildCtsPageMetadata` automatically:
- Reads `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` env var (defaults to `https://chinatravel.co.nz`) for all absolute URLs
- Sets `alternates.canonical` to the absolute page URL
- Sets `openGraph.images` to 1200×630 absolute URL
- Sets `twitter.card: 'summary_large_image'`
- Sets `robots: { index: true, follow: true }` (override via `robots` param)

**Do NOT** write `alternates.canonical`, `openGraph.url`, or `openGraph.images` manually — the helper handles these.

### Environment Variable
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://chinatravel-zloe.onrender.com   # set in Render dashboard
# Default fallback (if not set): https://chinatravel.co.nz
```

### 2. Schema Markup — Pass to `<SchemaMarkup data={schema} />`
```typescript
// All guide pages use 3 schema types:
const schema = [
  { '@type': 'Article', headline: ..., datePublished: ..., author: ... },
  { '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [...] },
  { '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: guide.faqs.map(...) },
];
```

### 3. Never repeat titles/descriptions across pages
All 21 guide pages use `guide.metaTitle` and `guide.metaDescription` from `guides.ts`.

