## API Routes — Critical Rules

### Email (Resend)
```typescript
// ⚠️ CRITICAL: Resend MUST be instantiated INSIDE the handler, never at module level
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const resend = new Resend(process.env.RESEND_API_KEY); // ← INSIDE handler
  // ...
}
// If instantiated at module level → build-time crash on Render
```

### Environment Variables
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=...
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=...
RESEND_API_KEY=re_...  (not yet configured on Render)
```

---

## DestinationGuide Component

The `DestinationGuide.tsx` is used by all 21 guide pages. It has:
- Two-column layout: main content (2/3) + sticky sidebar (1/3)
- `GUIDE_CONFIG` map: maps each guide slug → hub URL, related tours, related guides
- Sections: Table of Contents → Intro → Mid-CTA → Sections → Attractions → Gallery → FAQs → Related Guides
- Sidebar: CTA card, Quick Facts, Featured Tours (with links), Useful Links

**When adding a new guide**, update `GUIDE_CONFIG` in `DestinationGuide.tsx` with:
```typescript
'new-destination-travel-guide': {
  hubUrl: '/destination-tours',
  hubLabel: 'All Destination Tours',
  relatedTours: [...],  // 2-3 TourCard objects
  relatedGuides: [...], // 4 GuideLink objects
},
```

---

## Image Conventions

### Next.js Image (required for all images)
```tsx
// Hero images — use fill + priority
<Image src={guide.heroImage} alt={guide.h1} fill priority sizes="100vw" className="object-cover" />

// Card thumbnails
<Image src={tour.image} alt={tour.name} fill sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw" className="object-cover" />
```

### Image Paths
```
/images/tours/          # Tour product images (44 images)
/images/guides/         # Guide page images
  /beijing/             # 9 images: forbidden-city-*, great-wall-*, beijing-*
  /shanghai/            # 5 images: shanghai-*
  /chengdu/             # 2 images: chengdu-*
  /guilin/              # 2 images: guilin-*
  /[other-guides]/      # Each has hero.jpg + 1-2 supporting images
```

⚠️ Never use CSS `background-image` for above-the-fold images — use Next.js `<Image>` with `fill`.

---

## Tour Data Structure

```typescript
interface Tour {
  slug: string;
  destination: 'china' | 'japan' | 'vietnam';
  tier: 'signature' | 'discovery' | 'stopover';
  name: string;         // Format: "China Signature — Silk Road Discovery"
  tagline: string;
  duration: string;     // "17 Days"
  price: string;        // "From NZD $6,699"
  heroImage: string;    // "/images/tours/..."
  highlights: string[];
  itinerary: DayItinerary[];
  inclusions: string[];
  exclusions: string[];
}

// Tour URL structure
/tours/[destination]/[tier]/[slug]
// e.g. /tours/china/signature/silk-road
```

---

## Guide Data Structure

```typescript
interface DestinationGuide {
  id: string;
  slug: string;              // 'beijing-travel-guide'
  destinationName: string;   // 'Beijing'
  metaTitle: string;         // 50-60 chars for SEO
  metaDescription: string;   // 140-160 chars for SEO
  keywords: string[];
  h1: string;
  heroSubtitle: string;
  heroImage: string;         // '/images/guides/[dest]/hero.jpg'
  introText: string[];       // 3 paragraphs
  sections: Section[];       // 4-6 sections
  attractions: Attraction[]; // 4-8 attractions
  practicalInfo: PracticalInfo;
  faqs: FAQ[];               // exactly 5 FAQs
  relatedTourSlugs: string[];
  relatedGuideSlugs: string[];
  galleryImages: string[];   // 5-8 images
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
}
```

---

## Common Tasks

### Add a new destination guide
1. Add data object to `src/lib/data/guides.ts`
2. Create `src/app/[slug]/page.tsx` using the standard template (copy any existing guide page)
3. Add entry to `GUIDE_CONFIG` in `DestinationGuide.tsx`
4. Add to `sitemap.ts` guide list
5. Create image directory `public/images/guides/[dest]/` with `hero.jpg`
6. Commit: `feat: add [destination] travel guide`

### Add a new tour
1. Add tour object to `src/lib/data/tours.ts`
2. Add to `sitemap.ts` tour list
3. Add to `GUIDE_CONFIG` relatedTours for relevant guide pages
4. Commit: `feat: add [tour-name] tour`

### Debug build failures
1. Run `npm run build` locally
2. Common causes:
   - Resend at module level → move inside handler
   - Missing guide data → add to guides.ts
   - Wrong image path → check public/images/
   - TypeScript type mismatch → check interfaces in tours.ts / guides.ts

---

## Git Workflow

```bash
# Branch: always main
git add -A
git commit -m "feat: description"   # or fix:, refactor:, docs:, chore:
git push origin main                 # triggers Render auto-deploy

# Common commit types:
# feat:     new page or feature
# fix:      bug fix
# refactor: code restructuring (no behavior change)
# docs:     documentation only
# chore:    config, tooling
```

---

## What NOT to do

- ❌ Never use CSS `background-image` for hero images — use `<Image fill priority>`
- ❌ Never instantiate Resend at module level — always inside the handler
- ❌ Never use the same `title`/`description` across multiple pages
- ❌ Never add `<img>` tags — always use Next.js `<Image>`
- ❌ Never hardcode domain URLs in metadata — always use `buildCtsPageMetadata()` (reads `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`)
- ❌ Never modify `guides-complete.ts` or `guides-rest.ts` — those are deleted; `guides.ts` is the only source
- ❌ Never skip the sitemap when adding new pages

---

## ⚠️ DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW — MANDATORY

### TEST-DRIVEN DEVELOPMENT (TDD)
ALL features and bug fixes MUST follow TDD:

```
1. RED: Write failing test
   └─ npm test → test FAILS

2. GREEN: Implement minimal code
   └─ npm test → test PASSES

3. REFACTOR: Clean up code
   └─ npm test → test still PASSES

4. VERIFY: Coverage ≥ 80%
   └─ npm test --coverage
```

**Test File Locations:**
- Unit tests: `src/**/__tests__/[filename].test.ts`
- Integration tests: `src/__tests__/integration/`
- E2E tests: `e2e/` (critical user flows)

**Required Test Coverage:**
- ✅ Unit tests for all functions/components
- ✅ Integration tests for API routes
- ✅ E2E tests for critical user journeys
- ✅ Minimum 80% coverage (measure with `npm test --coverage`)

---

### CODE REVIEW CHECKLIST
Before pushing ANY code, verify ALL items:

**🔒 Security**
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets (API keys, tokens, passwords)
- [ ] No SQL injection (use parameterized queries only)
- [ ] No XSS vulnerabilities (escape user input)
- [ ] No CSRF protection bypass
- [ ] No exposed PII in error messages or logs
- [ ] All user inputs validated at system boundaries

**✅ Functionality**
- [ ] All tests passing (100% pass rate)
- [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%
- [ ] No `console.log` or debug statements remaining
- [ ] Error handling explicit (no silent failures)
- [ ] No unhandled promise rejections
- [ ] All edge cases covered

**📝 Code Quality**
- [ ] Functions < 50 lines (split if longer)
- [ ] Files < 800 lines (extract modules)
- [ ] No nesting deeper than 4 levels
- [ ] Descriptive names (no `x`, `temp`, `data`)
- [ ] DRY principle (no code duplication)
- [ ] Proper TypeScript types (no `any`)
- [ ] Imports organized (React → lib → components)

**⚡ Performance**
- [ ] No N+1 queries
- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders
- [ ] Images optimized with Next.js Image
- [ ] Bundle size acceptable

**🔍 SEO (for public pages)**
- [ ] Metadata configured (title, description, keywords)
- [ ] JSON-LD schema included (if applicable)
- [ ] Open Graph tags present
- [ ] Canonical URLs correct
- [ ] Internal links included (min 3-5 per page)
- [ ] Alt text on all images

**♿ Accessibility**
- [ ] All images have descriptive alt text
- [ ] Form labels properly associated
- [ ] Color contrast sufficient (WCAG AA)
- [ ] Keyboard navigation functional
- [ ] Semantic HTML used (`<button>`, `<nav>`, etc.)

